# SprintCycle Architecture (slim) / 架构边界（精简）

Full reference: `docs/CURSOR_ARCHITECTURE_ORCHESTRATION.md` and `docs/ARCHITECTURE_INVARIANTS.md`.  
完整参考见上述文档。

## Core principles / 核心原则

- Thin public facade (`api.py`): normalize, route, delegate, aggregate — **no workflow logic**. (薄门面，不含工作流逻辑。)
- Strict separation: execution, governance, observability, suggestions, deploy/runtime, evolution. (严格分层。)
- Reuse existing services, facades, hooks, registries, adapters — no parallel pipelines. (复用现有扩展点。)
- Composition root: `application/composition/http_factory.py` wires only; adapters live in `infrastructure/adapters/`. (组合根只组装。)
- DDD: immutable Aggregate Roots, stateless Domain Services, ports in `domain/ports/` (17 ports). (DDD 不变性。)

## Non-negotiable boundaries / 不可协商边界

- No domain rules in API, HTTP handlers, or Console Web orchestration. (领域规则不进 API/UI。)
- No bypassing hooks (lifecycle/policy) or facades (domain coordination). (不绕过 hook/facade。)
- No duplicate governance/observability/suggestion logic in execution code. (执行层不重复治理逻辑。)
- No compatibility shims as primary architecture (except documented command shims like `speckit.md`). (不以兼容层为主架构。)
- No mutable aggregates; cross-aggregate refs by ID only. (聚合根不可变，跨聚合用 ID。)
- Application layer uses ports only — no direct infrastructure imports outside composition root. (应用层只依赖端口。)
- Use `LifecycleStateMachine` with `context="lifecycle"|"execution"` — no separate ExecutionStateMachine. (统一状态机。)
- LangGraph is orchestration adapter under `infrastructure/adapters/generic/integrations/langgraph/` — not domain owner. (LangGraph 为编排适配器。)

## Layer stack / 层级

```
interfaces/http → application → domain → infrastructure
```

| Layer | Owns |
|-------|------|
| `interfaces/http/` | HTTP adaptation, middleware |
| `application/services/` | Use cases, workflow coordination |
| `domain/core/` | Aggregates, value objects, domain services |
| `infrastructure/adapters/` | Port implementations |

## Lifecycle chain / 生命周期链

`intent entry → plan/prepare → sprint orchestration → SprintOrchestrator → observe/repair → deliver → governance/suggestions → evolution`

Backbone: `ReleasePlan → SprintOrchestrator.execute_release_plan → SprintExecutor`.  
Web-initiated tasks must complete this chain stably. (Web 触发须稳定走完闭环。)

## Console Web / 控制台边界

Dashboard translates user intent into contract operations; it must **not** own stage transitions, governance, promotion, or repair logic. (控制台不拥有编排逻辑。)

## LangGraph / 编排

Scope: `plan / run / observe / repair`. Graph nodes call services/facades — no domain rules inside nodes. (图节点只编排，不调领域规则。)

## Change strategy / 变更策略

1. Identify owning subsystem and layer. (识别所属子系统。)
2. Prefer nearest extension point (service, facade, hook, registry, adapter). (优先最近扩展点。)
3. Smallest change in the correct layer; verify E2E lifecycle + governance flows. (最小变更并验证闭环。)
4. Register new infrastructure only in composition root via port factories. (基础设施仅在组合根注册。)

When in doubt: preserve architecture, extend don't replace. (存疑时保架构、扩展而非替换。)
